<item>
            <title>[LU-19073] lgss_sk should handle ASCII-encoded SSK keys</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19073</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For ease of use, it was proposed that the SSK keys could be ASCII-encoded (e.g. base64 or &lt;tt&gt;gss_base64url_encode()&lt;/tt&gt;) so that they can be more easily processed by user tools (e.g. copy-paste from EMF SSK generator web interface or similar).  &lt;tt&gt;lgss_sk&lt;/tt&gt; and other tools should be able to transparently detect the ASCII-encoded key format (e.g. by some string at the beginning, like &quot;&lt;tt&gt;Lustre SSK v1.0\n&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; ) and decode it into the current binary struct format in memory (after skipping the descriptive string).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
