                            <comment id="466738" author="sebastien" created="Fri, 8 Aug 2025 08:55:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think generating the ASCII-encoded SSK key could be done via a new &lt;tt&gt;&amp;#45;a|&amp;#45;&amp;#45;ascii&lt;/tt&gt; option to lgss_sk:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://doc.lustre.org/lustre_manual.xhtml#table.lgss_sk_params&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://doc.lustre.org/lustre_manual.xhtml#table.lgss_sk_params&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Having a header such as &quot;&lt;tt&gt;Lustre SSK v1.0\n&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; would be fine, and allow lgss_sk and the internal loading function &lt;tt&gt;sk_load_keyfile()&lt;/tt&gt; to discriminate between a binary SSK key and an ASCII-encoded SSK key.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
